# Helix Bank — LaunchDarkly SE Technical Homework
# Copy this file to `app/.env.local` and fill in real values.
# `.env.local` is gitignored — never commit secrets.

# --- LaunchDarkly client SDK ---
# The browser SDK initialises with this. Safe to expose to the client bundle.
# Source: LD Console → Account settings → Projects → default → Environments → test → click key icon next to "Client-side ID"
NEXT_PUBLIC_LD_CLIENT_SIDE_ID=

# --- LaunchDarkly server SDK ---
# Used by /api/perk-allocation/generate for AI Config evaluation (server-side).
# Keep secret — never expose to the client.
# Source: same panel as above, "SDK key" field.
LD_SDK_KEY=

# --- LaunchDarkly REST API token (writer scope) ---
# Used by /api/perk-allocation/apply to PATCH the `applied-perk-allocation`
# flag value via REST. Without this, applies persist to the in-memory store
# only (lost on server restart / cold start).
# Source: LD Console → Account settings → Authorization → Access tokens → Create token
#         Name: helix-demo-applied-state-writer
#         Role: Writer (or Custom with updateFeatureFlag + updateFlagVariations on this flag)
#         Service token: yes
LAUNCHDARKLY_API_TOKEN=

# --- Anthropic API key ---
# Used by /api/perk-allocation/generate for live Claude Haiku 4.5 calls.
# Without this, the route returns pre-canned per-strategy stub allocations
# (still routed through the AI Config so variation assignment is exercised;
# only the actual LLM invocation is substituted).
# Source: console.anthropic.com → API Keys → Create Key
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# --- (Optional) OpenAI API key ---
# Reserved for when the perk-allocation-strategist AI Config raises
# `gpt-4o-mini-balanced` above 0% allocation (the "live cross-provider raise"
# playback moment). Without this, the GPT variation path falls back to stub.
# Source: platform.openai.com → API keys
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
